The paper focuses on sketch-based modeling, which involves creating 3D shapes from 2D drawings. This falls under the category of computer graphics (cs.GR). The approach proposed in the paper involves the use of deep convolutional neural networks (CNNs) to predict 3D shapes from 2D drawings, which involves computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the training of the CNNs using synthetic contour drawings and procedurally-generated abstract shapes, which involves machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper presents a minimal modeling interface that allows users to draw and refine 3D shapes, which involves human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
